<div id='communityQuestionsWithAnswers'>
<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/646970-why-doesn-t-inspector-gamache-like-yvette">Why doesn&#39;t Inspector Gamache like Yvette Nichol? What exactly did she do wrong?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_646970'><a id="like_count_community_question_646970" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/646970?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">5 likes</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F13539460-still-life">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/646970-why-doesn-t-inspector-gamache-like-yvette">5 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/646970-why-doesn-t-inspector-gamache-like-yvette">See all 16 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/7930679-fred"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1330735738i/7930679._UX100_CR0,21,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/7930679-fred">Fred</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">As a reader, I wanted to like Yvette Nichol. She put herself under a lot of stress to be seen as a success to her family, her co-workers, and — most o<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">As a reader, I wanted to like Yvette Nichol. She put herself under a lot of stress to be seen as a success to her family, her co-workers, and — most of all — to herself. But that same drive for success limited her ability to listen, learn and reflect. She is completely self-centered. Gamache takes her under his wing, truly trying to help her find the success she strives for. When he tries to explain things to her — using whatever means he has available — she gets upset before hearing him out. I really wanted for her to see the light, but as the story progressed, she became irredeemably irritating.<br /><br />Somewhere in the book a line from 'Julius Caesar' appears in conversation between Myrna and Gamache: “The fault, dear Brutus, lies not in our stars, but in ourselves that we are underlings.” Myrna replies to Gamache that “The vast majority of troubled people don’t get it. The fault is here [within us], but so is the solution. That’s the grace. … Who among us can admit that the problem is us?” So true in poor Yvette Nichol’s case. <br /><a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerFooter'>

